<div class='documentTop'><div>
  
  
    <h1>Business environment and innovation system</h1>
  
  </div></div>
  

  <div class="documentBody" id="Tekstinnhold">   
  <div>
    <p>&nbsp;<img alt="" src="/upload/KRD/Temabilder/REGA/bedrifter_naeringsmijo.jpg" align="top" /></p>
<p><strong>Rural and regional policy aims at developing local and regional business environments and systems that improve the prerequisites for added value based on innovation. The initiatives implemented must be customised to suit regional challenges.</strong> </p>
<p>One common characteristic for growth regions is strong commercial clusters and innovative environments. <br /><br />Companies, educational and research groups and diverse public bodies work together, forming a dynamic development environment. The existence of a regional competence and innovation infrastructure is therefore an important&nbsp;element for increasing added value in different regions. Isolation from centres of expertise and the larger markets is a challenge for commerce and industry in many parts of Norway. </p>
<ul>
<li>&nbsp;<a href="http://ekstranett.innovasjonnorge.no/templates/Page_Meta.aspx?id=57487" target="_blank">The Arena Programme</a></li>
<li>&nbsp;<a href="http://ekstranett.innovasjonnorge.no/templates/Page_Meta.aspx?id=56522" target="_blank">Norwegian Centres of Expertise</a></li></ul>
  </div>
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
